b_tcp_accept: accept() failed: Error 0 (0).</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">------------------------------------------------------------</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">A process or daemon was unable to complete a TCP connection</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">to another process:</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">&nbsp; Local host: &nbsp; &nbsp;pcp-j-19</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">&nbsp; Remote host: &nbsp; 172.18.0.119</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">This is usually caused by a firewall on the remote host. Please</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">check that any firewall (e.g., iptables) has been disabled and</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">try again.</font></div><div class=""><font face="courier new, monospace" size="1" class="">------------------------------------------------------------</font></div></div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br class=""></div><div class="gmail_extra">Let me know what sort of verbose options I should use to gather any additional info you may need.</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br class=""></div><div class="gmail_extra">-Paul</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br class=""><div class="gmail_quote">On Fri, Oct 31, 2014 at 7:14 PM, Ralph Castain <span dir="ltr" class="">&lt;<a href="mailto:rhc.openmpi@gmail.com" target="_blank" class="">rhc.openmpi@gmail.com</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br class=""><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex"><div style="word-wrap:break-word" class="">Hi folks<div class=""><br class=""></div><div class="">I know 1.8.4 isn’t entirely complete just yet, but I’d like to get a head start 